'''Mahmoud Nayef Mardi Al-Hwaitat''' ({{langx|ar|مَحْمُود نَايِف مَرْضِيّ الحويطات}}; born 6 October 1993) is a Jordanian [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|winger]] for the Jordanian club [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==

=== Ittihad Al-Zarqa ===
On July 2013, Al-Mardi began his professional career at [[Ittihad Al-Zarqa SC|Ittihad Al-Zarqa]].

==== Al-Sheikh Hussein (loan) ====
On 2 January 2014, Mahmoud was loaned out to [[Al-Sheikh Hussein SC|Al-Sheikh Hussein]] until the end of the season.

=== Ittihad Al-Ramtha ===
On 29 May 2014, Mahmoud joined [[Ittihad Al-Ramtha SC|Ittihad Al-Ramtha]].

=== Al-Ahli (Amman) ===
On 2 January 2015, Mahmoud moved to [[Al-Ahli SC (Amman)|Al-Ahli]].

=== Al-Arabi (Kuwait) ===
On 11 September 2017, Al-Mardi joined [[Kuwait Premier League]] club [[Al-Arabi SC (Kuwait)|Al-Arabi]].

=== Al-Faisaly ===
After a short stint at Al-Arabi, Al-Mardi was then transferred to Jordanian powerhouse [[Al-Faisaly SC|Al-Faisaly]] on 23 December 2017. Mahmoud helped the club to win the cup double; the [[2018–19 Jordanian Pro League]] and the [[2018–19 Jordan FA Cup]].

=== Al-Jazeera ===
On 1 August 2018. Al-Mardi joined [[Al-Jazeera SC (Amman)|Al-Jazeera]]. He scored his first goal for the club on 2 April 2019 against his former club, Al-Ahli in a 4–0 win.

=== Oman Club ===
On 24 January 2021, Al-Mardi moved to [[Oman Professional League|Oman Elite League]] side [[Oman Club]].

=== Al-Salt ===
Al-Mardi's stint was cut short and on 15 April 2021, he moved back to his native country to join [[Al-Salt SC|Al-Salt]].

=== Al-Muharraq ===
On 23 August 2021, Al-Mardi transferred to Bahraini club [[Al-Muharraq SC|Al-Muharraq]], where he was listed in the team's [[2021 AFC Cup]] squad. Al-Mardi would go on to have a brilliant form throughout the cup where in the semi-finals, he scored a goal against [[Kuwait SC]] resulting in a 2–0 victory sending the club to the AFC Cup Final. During the final on 5 November 2021, Mahmoud broke the deadlock early on in the 2' minute against [[FC Nasaf]] where they would eventually carry the 2021 AFC Cup trophy. Al-Mardi also won the [[Bahraini FA Cup|2021 Bahraini FA Cup]] during his time at the club.

===Kedah Darul Aman===
On 19 June 2022, Al-Mardi moved to Southeast Asia to sign for [[Malaysia Super League]] club [[Kedah Darul Aman F.C.|Kedah Darul Aman]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hmetro.com.my/arena/bola-sepak/2022/06/853730/kedah-sambar-pemain-jordan-mahmoud-al-mardi|title=kedah sambar pemain jordan mahmoud al-mardi|date=20 June 2022 |language=ms-MY|access-date=2022-07-01}}</ref> In his second match for the club, he scored a hat-trick against Cambodian club [[Visakha FC|Visakha]] in the [[2022 AFC Cup]] group stage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stadiumastro.com/bola-sepak/piala-afc-hatrik-mahmoud-almardi-bawa-kedah-ke-separuh-akhir-zon-asean-217427|title=piala afc hatrik mahmoud almardi bawa kedah ke separuh akhir zon asean|website=www.stadiumastro.com/|language=ms-MY|access-date=2022-07-01}}</ref>

=== Qadsia ===
After the 2022 Malaysia Super League concluded, Al-Mardi returned to Kuwait to join [[Qadsia SC|Qadsia]].

=== Al-Hussein (Irbid) ===
On 21 May 2023, Al-Mardi moved back to Jordan to join [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]].

==== Dibba (loan) ====
Al-Mardi joined [[UAE Pro League]] club [[Dibba FC|Dibba]] on a one-year loan.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Fadel |first1=Mohammed |title=دبا يضم اللاعب الأردني محمود المرضي على سبيل الإعارة |url=https://www.emaratalyoum.com/sports/local/2025-07-04-1.1957227 |website=emaratalyoum.com |publisher=Emarat Al-Youm |access-date=17 August 2025 |location=Fujairah |language=Arabic |date=4 July 2025}}</ref>

====Return to Al-Hussein====
On 15 January 2026, Al-Mardi returned to Al-Hussein, after terminating his contract with Dibba by mutual consent.<ref>{{cite web |title=يعود إلى بيته.. الحسين يستعيد نجم النشامى محمود مرضي |url=https://royanews.tv/news/371764/%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B7%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%82%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%87%D9%8A-%D9%88%D9%86%D9%83%D9%88%D9%86%D9%83%D9%88..-%22%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A9%22-%D8%AE%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%81%D9%8A%D9%86 |website=royanews.tv |publisher=Roya News |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=15 January 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=هل اضطر محمود المرضي للعودة إلى ناديه الحسين إربد؟ |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D9%87%D9%84-%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%B7%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%B6%D9%8A-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A5%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%AF%D8%9F |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=15 January 2026}}</ref>

== International career ==
Mahmoud's first match with the Jordan national senior team was against [[Kyrgyzstan national football team|Kyrgyzstan]] on 15 September 2015 during the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]], which resulted in a 0–0 draw. On 11 January 2018, he scored his first goal for his country in a friendly match against [[Finland national football team|Finland]].

Mahmoud was called up to the [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup]] in which he scored against [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] in the 5–1 victory during the group stage.

